        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/ac8455/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-09-07T14:35:57.877Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Related to <span class=\"hashtag-raw\">#71488</span>.</p>\n<p>When Signal notices that a contact has deregistered, this should be noted and presented to the user in a variety of ways:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>The chat stream list should show the preexisting chat with that user with a strong mark indicating that it is ‚Äúdead‚Äù.  (e.g. I like a big X over the avatar). All other UI points at which that contacts avatar is displayed should always be labeled with that marker.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Upon noticing that a contact is deregistered, all admins of all groups it belongs to should see a message like ‚ÄúGroup member Jane Doe is no longer using Signal‚Äù in the chat stream (in fine print, like other control messages).  Perhaps there should be a group option to allow all group members to see this (good for small groups, bad for big groups).  Otherwise, People otherwise have no idea that their messages they‚Äôd been expecting Jane to see, Jane is no longer seeing.  Nothing in the group chat alerts users that, ‚Äúthe message you just sent isn‚Äôt going to be seen by Jane.‚Äù  Currently, the only possible way to know is before sending any group chat message, check the individual message chat for each member to see if it reports ‚Äúnot using Signal‚Äù.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>When looking at the profile of a deregistered user John Doe, some button like ‚ÄúRemove Jane Doe user from all groups for which I am admin‚Äù should be available.  Also a button like ‚ÄúAdd a selected user to all groups that Jane Doe is in‚Äù (this would be generally useful, but especially when I just need to then select Jane Doe‚Äôs new account).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Do not display the read receipt checkmark for a group chat message, if some of its members have stopped using Signal.  The message has not been read by them.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>",
